  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (MRL 3, W-EP-04 trigger)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. Model Risk Level is 3. Thirteen credibility factors are addressed; twelve are formally assessed with requiredLevel and achievedLevel populated. One factor — Equivalency of input parameters — carries factorStatus 'not-assessed' because the assessment team argued, in the rationale narrative, that input parameter equivalency is irrelevant to a purely predictive COU with no physical comparator experiment. This argument would properly be encoded as 'not-applicable', but the package encodes it as 'not-assessed', leaving a material epistemic gap at MRL 3. Decision is Accepted, making the gap non-obvious to a quick reviewer.",
  "modelRiskLevel": 3,
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
