      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "SQA plan documented; version control and regression testing in place for solver release used.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (OpenFOAM v9) is maintained under a documented SQA plan with version-controlled source, automated regression tests covering relevant solver modules, and a documented build verification procedure. Achieved level meets required level for MRL 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy tests on canonical flows confirm solver convergence rates consistent with formal order.",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions applied to rotating-frame Navier-Stokes equations; observed spatial order of accuracy is 1.97 (expected 2.0 for second-order scheme). Temporal convergence verified on lid-driven cavity benchmark. Achieved level satisfies MRL 3 requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation-based GCI reported for primary QoI (hemolysis index) on three systematically refined meshes.",
      "rationale": "Three meshes (4.2M, 9.8M, 21.4M cells) used; GCI for hemolysis index is 4.1% on the medium mesh selected for production runs. Discretization uncertainty is within the 5% tolerance established for MRL 3. Achieved level meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, rotational speed, fluid temperature, hematocrit) match simulation inputs within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Inlet flow rates and rotational speeds were matched within 1.5% and 0.3% respectively. However, hematocrit in bench experiments ranged 36–42% while the simulation used a fixed 40% value; temperature variation (±2°C) was not propagated into model inputs. These gaps reduce the achieved level to 2, below the required level of 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative agreement metric (E%) between predicted and measured hemolysis index reported with uncertainty bounds for all 5 operating points.",
      "rationale": "Mean absolute error across 5 operating points is 18.3% with 95% confidence interval ±6.1%. Two operating points exceed the 15% agreement threshold. Experimental uncertainty (±12% on hemolysis index measurement) partially explains the discrepancy, but the achieved level is assessed as 2 because systematic over-prediction at high flow rates is unexplained."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) is the same metric used in the regulatory submission and clinical acceptance threshold.",
      "rationale": "The simulation directly outputs NIH (g/100 L) which is the quantity specified in the device submission and compared against the clinical threshold of 0.01 g/100 L. No surrogate or proxy metric is used. Achieved level meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments performed on the FDA generic pump geometry at operating conditions spanning the VAD COU envelope.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the FDA generic centrifugal pump, which shares impeller topology with the device but differs in volute geometry and gap dimensions. Operating conditions cover 4 of 5 COU flow-speed points; the highest-speed point (6000 RPM, 2 L/min) was not included in validation experiments due to cavitation risk in the test rig. Achieved level is 2 due to partial coverage and geometric discrepancy."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence demonstrated by residual reduction of at least 4 orders of magnitude and monitored QoI stabilization over final 500 iterations.",
      "rationale": "All simulations achieve residual reduction of 5–6 orders of magnitude. Hemolysis index monitored over the final 1000 iterations shows variation less than 0.3%. Solver error contribution is negligible relative to discretization uncertainty. Achieved level meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst; boundary condition files and mesh generation scripts archived and version-controlled.",
      "rationale": "An independent CFD analyst reviewed the simulation setup, boundary condition specification, and post-processing scripts. No errors were identified. All input files are archived in the project repository with commit hashes recorded in the assessment report. Achieved level meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model selection (turbulence closure, hemolysis power-law model) justified by comparison with alternatives and sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-ω turbulence model was selected based on prior literature for rotating machinery. A sensitivity study comparing SST k-ω and realizable k-ε showed hemolysis index differences of up to 22% at high-speed operating points. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model was used without comparison to the modified Bludszuweit or strain-based models. Model form uncertainty is not fully characterized, reducing achieved level to 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material properties and boundary condition values traceable to measurement data or published standards with stated uncertainties.",
      "rationale": "Blood viscosity modeled as non-Newtonian (Carreau-Yasuda) with parameters from Merrill et al. (1965) and confirmed by internal rheometry data. Pump geometry dimensions taken from manufacturer drawings with dimensional inspection report. Inlet velocity profiles derived from Doppler ultrasound measurements. All inputs documented with source traceability in the simulation data package."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Blood samples characterized for hematocrit, donor demographics, and storage age; minimum 3 independent donors per operating point.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis experiments used bovine blood from 4 independent donors per operating point. Hematocrit 38–42%, storage age ≤5 days. Sample characterization meets the required level for MRL 3. Donor-to-donor variability is reported as part of experimental uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Demonstrate that simulation input parameters (geometry, fluid properties, boundary conditions) are equivalent to those of the validation experiment within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "The assessment team determined that equivalency of input parameters does not apply to this COU because the simulation is used in a purely predictive mode without a paired physical experiment for the production device geometry. The team reasoned that parameter equivalency is only meaningful when a direct simulation-to-experiment comparison is being made, and that the validation activities already address this implicitly through the output comparison factor. Consequently, no formal equivalency assessment was conducted and no requiredLevel or achievedLevel was assigned. Note: this reasoning would properly justify a factorStatus of 'not-applicable'; encoding it as 'not-assessed' leaves an unresolved epistemic gap at MRL 3 because the factor's absence has not been formally justified through the scoping process."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/vad-mrl3-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors were formally assessed. Seven factors achieved their required levels; five factors fell one gradation below required levels, which the team judged acceptable given the conservative hemolysis threshold margin (predicted NIH 0.0041 g/100 L versus threshold 0.01 g/100 L, a 59% margin). The equivalency of input parameters factor was not assessed on the basis that it was considered inapplicable to a predictive COU; this judgment was accepted by the team without formal scoping documentation. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification confirms that the 95th-percentile hemolysis prediction remains below the clinical threshold. The overall credibility package is accepted at assurance level Medium for MRL 3.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
